title: Marilyn Manson Teasing New Album 'Say10' In Cryptic Video [News]
text:
Marilyn Manson Teasing New Album 'Say10' in Cryptic Video It did miss its originally planned release date after all... Posted 11 hours ago 3 
Marilyn Manson missed his originally planned Valentine's Day release date last month for his new album "Say10" without nary an explanation. 
Just recently (March 22nd) he shared the following cryptic video with a caption citing "6:19", which some have interpreted to be a reference to bible. 
Admittedly though, the vague reference could cite a number of different passages. 
One thing's for sure, June 19th, isn't a Friday - the traditional release day favored by the music industry - making it unlikely that is is a release date. Публикация от Marilyn Manson (@marilynmanson) Мар 22 2017 в 6:18 PDT
